---
description: Security rules for Rails todo app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never write, log, or expose secrets, API keys, or credentials.
- Never use eval on user input.
- Never use html_safe or raw on untrusted input.
- Always use parameterized queries instead of SQL string interpolation.
- Do not disable CSRF protection.
- Do not bypass strong parameters or mass assignment protections.
- Do not disable Rails session security checks.
- Validate and sanitize user input appropriately.
